data.description: Gorgeous Martin Park, home to Motown's iconic Gladys Knight & Martha Reeves.  Centered around University of Detroit Mercy and rich with history this neighborhood is filled with elegant post war single family homes.  This home sits on a large quiet corner with a 2 car garage and backyard all set for entertaining. It has well preserved character  including crown moulding, hardwood floors, crosshatch ceramic tile bathroom floors  & details. A double built in oven frees up kitchen space and the breakfast nook is ideal for busy mornings. This family home has all the beauty you want in a historic home coupled with the modernized amenities central air and updated household systems.
